      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C fan. Butter and line the tin. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{mixed-spice}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}, then stir in the {{whole-milk}}. Fold in the {{apple-eating}} pieces.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top and bake, 45 to 50 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon the batter into the tin and level the surface. Scatter the {{demerara-sugar}} evenly over the top. This is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "demerara crust",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9ygsk200004ov47kd5l7co"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": the crystals will caramelise and stay slightly crunchy after baking. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean and the top feels firm when pressed. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes before turning out. Serve in wedges.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
